result.name: YUM CHA (Causeway Bay)

reviews.text:
Food is good, 1/4 of the menu not available but that’s okay but even from the menu that was available, some items were not available. 

Like we’re going to Yum cha...shouldn’t you have everything on menu ready to go? 

The waiters and waitresses should smile...show us a fake smile would be better than nothing...

July 2019
Update as I went again with some friends and this time was a bit better

funny and creative dishes. you are willing to pay a bit more than the local dumsum restaurant,  but in return you have good service and cozy environment.  if you have friends in town or business contact , it's a suitable place.
A bit on the expensive side. But the food and service was good. I'd definitely recommend the Truffle noodles.
cute dimsum. taste was good. just very noisy at the restaurant.
Good food, am glad that they introduced new dim sum items.  Service was good, will be wonderful if they can be more cheerful 😃
